Author: ComputerGenie 👴🏼📢#7004
Content:
it's not in the column because bash is telling you that there's something in the code that will not accept that to print
that's why it says "invalid number"

Author: ComputerGenie 👴🏼📢#7004
Content: 'line 143' <- that's bash telling you where it sees the issue (which may or may not actually be line 143, depending on the amount of whitespace in the script)
